#
# This function fits lasso regression with responses y and design matrix X.
#
function lsqlasso(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64}, λ::Float64=0.0;
                  grouplabel::Vector{Int}=[0:size(X, 2)-1],
                  sqrtlasso::Bool=false)

  # Find unique groups
  grplist = unique(grouplabel[grouplabel .!= 0])
  ngrp = length(grplist)

  # Create optimization variables
  βhat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  t = Variable(ngrp)
  # Set up optmization problem
  if sqrtlasso
    problem = minimize(norm(y - X * βhat) + λ * sum(t))
  else
    problem = minimize(0.5 * sum_squares(y - X * βhat) + λ * sum(t))
  end
  for g = 1:ngrp
    grpidx = find(grouplabel .== grplist[g])
    problem.constraints += sqrt(countnz(grpidx)) * norm(βhat[grpidx]) <= t[g]
  end
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  βhat.value

end

#
# This function computes SVM solution with responses y
# and design matrix X
#
function svm(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64}, λ::Float64, p::Float64=2.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  βhat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  if p == 1.0
    # 1-norm SVM
    problem = minimize(sum(pos(1.0 - y .* (X * βhat)))
                       + λ * norm(βhat[2:end], 1))
  elseif p == 2.0
    # regular SVM
    problem = minimize(sum(pos(1.0 - y .* (X * βhat)))
                       + λ * sum_squares(βhat[2:end]))
  end
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  βhat.value

end

#
# This function denoise images by total variation regularizaiton. Given image Y,
# it finds X such that minimizes 0.5 * vecnorm(Y - X)^2 + lambda * norm(D * X, 1),
# where D is the smoothing matrix.
#
function tvreg(Y::Matrix{Float64}, λ::Float64; penalty::String="anisotropic")

  # Image size
  m, n = size(Y)
  p = m * n

  if penalty == "anisotropic"

    # Create optimization variables
    X = Variable(size(Y))
    # Set up optimization problem
    problem = minimize(0.5sum_squares(Y - X) + λ *
                         (vecnorm(X[1:end-1, :] - X[2:end, :], 1) +
                          vecnorm(X[:, 1:end-1] - X[:, 2:end], 1)))

#     # This approach takes forever
#     # Create optimization variables
#     X = Variable(size(Y))
#     t = Variable(size(Y))
#     # Set up optmization problem
#     problem = minimize(0.5 * sum_squares(Y - X) + λ * sum(t))
#     for j = 1:n
#       for i = 1:m
#         if i < m && j < n
#           problem.constraints +=
#             abs(X[i, j] - X[i+1, j]) + abs(X[i, j] - X[i, j+1]) <= t[i, j]
#         elseif i == m && j < n
#           problem.constraints += abs(X[i, j] - X[i, j+1]) <= t[i, j]
#         elseif i < m && j == n
#           problem.constraints += abs(X[i, j] - X[i+1, j]) <= t[i, j]
#         else
#           problem.constraints += t[i, j] == 0.0
#         end
#       end
#     end

  elseif penalty == "ROF"

    # Create optimization variables
    X = Variable(size(Y))
    t = Variable(size(Y))
    # Set up optmization problem
    problem = minimize(0.5 * sum_squares(Y - X) + λ * sum(t))
    for j = 1:n
      for i = 1:m
        if i < m && j < n
          problem.constraints +=
            norm([X[i, j] - X[i+1, j], X[i, j] - X[i, j+1]]) <= t[i, j]
        elseif i == m && j < n
          problem.constraints += abs(X[i, j] - X[i, j+1]) <= t[i, j]
        elseif i < m && j == n
          problem.constraints += abs(X[i, j] - X[i+1, j]) <= t[i, j]
        else
          problem.constraints += t[i, j] == 0.0
        end
      end
    end

  end


  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  X.value

end
